The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Taufel urges Aussies to tour Pak
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Taufel urges Aussies to tour Pak
                      
	Melbourne: Urging the Australian cricket team to stop worrying about safety in Pakistan, worlds leading umpire Simon Taufel, who also happens to be an Aussie, called on Ricky Pontings men to fearlessly tour the friendly nation for next months Champions Trophy.         
	Taufel said that never once in his half a dozen tours to Pakistan has he felt any threat. The three-time ICC Umpire of the Year said he has always come across friendly and warm people in the country. (PTI)                                                                                                                          
